description.text: I'm always terrified that I leave the apartment without my keys, locking myself out (Darn self-locking doors!). So I made a little holder that reminds me to take 'em before I leave.
Print, highlight words with some paint, attach to surface via adhesive of choice (I used double sided tape), hang keys and hope that you don't forget them.

This is a customizable card box with recycle symbol lid. It is for
Save The Planet Board Game , a free and open-source DIY cooperative board game. In the Save the Planet Game you and your family and friends can work together to save the planet to win, while learning how to save the planet in real life. The beginner option is appropriate for children 4 and up and the advanced option is a fun game for teens up to any age. This game is open-source so you are encouraged to build on it - make it better, add more good deeds, make a local deed list and make more advanced derivatives. Have fun!

It was quite a PIA to count out 15 BB's and manually drop them in 1 by 1.   So I created this "thing".  It "counts" the BB's and allows you to reload in seconds.

Printed using .27 layer height, 25% infill, 1 shell. Using Replicator 5.5 but with default speeds (printing small objects like this with acceleration I find melts the previous layer too much). Printed with full support, it's only required to support the inside of the bowl. I've printed this a few times a few of them had plastic "hairs" preventing BB flow.. a drill bit of the correct size cleared that up. Pull the spring loaded trigger and insert tool, position the tool so the BB's do not flow into the gun. Fill it to the top and take out any remaining BB's (top BB sticks out about 2mm). Tip the butt end of the gun down at about a 60 degree angle, move the loader to the front of the gun - BB's should drop right in. Original Tinkercad object:
https://www.tinkercad.com/things/bMy319N45M0-daisy-powerline-15xt-bb-loader I noticed a minor issue with my grouping/"holes" on tinkercad, it produced an indent in the half circle support. Please use the "fixed" STL. Tinkercad is updated
